oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Rugby Tennis Club
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: These people were original settlers of Rugby. In his book on Rugby, Thomas Hughes wrote "The Rugby Tennis Club consists to-day of seven members, five English and two native, and will probably reach two figures within a few days, on the return of the boys. Meantime the effect of their first practice has been that they have resolved putting a Cincinnati and Chattanooga papers offering to play a match- best out of five sets- with any club in the United States. Such are infant communities in these latitudes!"
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
